{
  "texts": [
    "Following an internal Assessment of the Code, the Commission itself issued a Guidance in May 2021 underlining how it should be improved in areas such as definitions, clearer procedures, imprecision around prohibited behaviours and lack of monitoring mechanisms [47,48].",
    "Self-assessment constrained transparency among data sharing restrictions to protect trade secrets and privacy [29].",
    "Moreover, oversight depended on irregular corporate disclosures lacking standardization.",
    "Thereby while acknowledging scale of threats, its remedies centered platforms rather than the impacted public.In response to some of the criticism faced, the Commission therefore introduced a strengthened and updated Code in 2022, expanding on previous partnerships by requiring signatories document procedures, data access protocols and effectiveness indicators [49].",
    "Stricter identity verification aims reducing influence operations and synthetic media usage, while efforts are underway to balance counterspeech quality with the plurality of views (as reflected in the DSA through DD and NTD)."
  ]
}